Subject: [bioinfo] PhD position in Statistical Genetics at the CNG

The French National Center for Genotyping (www.CNG.fr/en) and the Inserm U1078 lab propose a PhD position in Statistical Genetics to study rare variants and gene-environment interactions in complex human diseases. A summary can be found below and further details about the project can be provided for interested candidates.

Applications will go through a competitive recruitment process, called Irtelis, which will fund up to 20 PhD fellowships for a duration of 3 years starting end of 2014 at the Life Science Division of the French Alternative Energies and Atomic Energy Commission (www.CEA.fr/english-portal). 

Deadline for online application is Friday 21 of March, 2014, at noon CET (my guess!).

Then an ad-hoc committee will preselect applicants who will be invited from May 21 to 23 at the Saclay research center of CEA (near Paris) for:
- an interview with a panel of distinguished scientists (from CEA and affiliated universities),
- an informal chat with prospective PhD supervisors (poster session).
For non-local participants, low-cost travel expenses and accommodation will be covered by the DSV.
Successful candidates will be notified by Friday 23 of May, 2014.

The web page containing all the necessary information (PhD projects and application form) is available at: www-dsv.cea.fr/en/phd-program/program-presentation

Please, contact me if you would like to discuss this opportunity further (kazma@cng.fr or remi.kazma@gmail.com).

Rémi Kazma

Statistical Genetics @ CNG

